title: Pusha T Says "King Push" Dropping This Spring
text:
Home > Music > Pusha T Says "King Push" Dropping This Spring Pusha T Says "King Push" Dropping This Spring 30 0 Posted by Danny Schwartz , Feb 15, 2017 at 03:30pm Pusha season approaching... 
Pusha T 's release of King Push â€“ Darkest Before Dawn: The Prelude at the tail end of 2015 gave many fans the hope that King Push would drop soon thereafter. It did not. There is now a semblance of a timeline: in a new interview, Pusha mentioned that he plans to release King Push this spring. 
In 2016, he put out the summer single "Drug Dealers Anonymous" and a pair of tracks in October, "H.G.T.V." and "Circles." 
In the interview he added that Kanye West and Teyana Taylor are both working on their next albums. This statement goes against a recent statement by Kanye mentor Malik Yusef that the rapper is not currently working on any new music and rather is focused on his health and family.
